    <!-- Section 6: FAQ -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-6">YouTube English Learning FAQs</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Are YouTube English lessons free?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes, most YouTube channels that teach English offer their lessons completely free. Channels like BBC Learning English, EngVid, and TED-Ed publish full courses, grammar explanations, and vocabulary lessons at no cost. Some channels offer premium memberships or courses, but the core content is always free. You can learn everything from basic grammar to advanced conversation skills without spending a single dollar.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">How long does it take to learn English from YouTube?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The time it takes varies widely depending on your starting level and how consistently you study. Reaching conversational fluency typically takes 6 to 18 months of regular practice. Beginners who watch 30 minutes of targeted English content daily combined with active note-taking can reach intermediate level within 3 to 6 months. Advanced learners focusing on vocabulary expansion and native-level listening can continue improving indefinitely with structured practice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Can I learn English just from YouTube?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">YouTube alone can take you from beginner to intermediate level effectively. However, reaching advanced fluency typically requires additional practice methods like speaking with native speakers, writing essays, and receiving personalized feedback. The best approach combines YouTube lessons for structured learning with conversation practice on tutoring platforms like <a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">iTalki</a>, where you can apply what you learn with real feedback from qualified teachers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">What is the best YouTube channel for English grammar?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">EngVid is widely considered the best YouTube channel for English grammar. Teachers like Ronnie, Adam, and Jade explain complex grammar concepts in clear, entertaining ways with hundreds of lessons covering everything from basic tenses to advanced conditionals. EnglishClass101 also offers excellent structured grammar courses, while BBC Learning English provides British English grammar with professional production quality.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">How often should I watch English YouTube videos?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Consistency matters more than duration. Watching 20 to 30 minutes of English content every day produces better results than watching 3 hours once a week. Active watching, where you take notes and repeat phrases out loud, is far more effective than passive viewing. Set a specific time each day for your English practice and treat it like any other important appointment. Building a daily habit is the single most effective thing you can do for your language learning progress.</p>
      </div>
